			<span class="anthracite size13" contentbodystyle="Anthracite">To answer Aaron's question - the chain has a very large WAN.  Each hotel has  a private network connection ranging from a fractional T1 and larger. 

They had gone to an ASP-environment a few months before I arrived which used a ton of bandwidth.

Almost all over their transactions (reservations, etc) went through the centeral office too.   That pipe was running 70% capacity during heavy usage, and from the data that the ITD gave me - they actually hit 90% util around the holidays.  Folks, that's a LOT of bandwidth.

</span>
		</div>
           
