			<span class="anthracite size13" contentbodystyle="Anthracite">I don't really know where to go next, but the MAC address has been in my mind since the first time you mentioned it.  Was the span port on the wap setup so that it was only monitoring incoming traffic on wireless ports, or was any being transmitted?  If so, then another wireless device is nearby and could also explain you never mentioned seeing anyone/thing nearby.  It could also explain why the next door neighbor was having problems with wireless access.  Do the two MAC addresses match up?  Can you find out?  What were they seeing on their end?



On a different note, regarding internal/external employees, somebody internal would most definitely have had to be involved, even if only a "janitor".  The question to me would be did spam have anything to do with why it was placed their -- I would hope not.</span>
