<span class="pubdate size11 darkgray" title="2003-11-11 17:31:00Z">Nov 11, 2003</span>
                
                

            </div>
			<span class="anthracite size13" contentbodystyle="Anthracite">Of course, the question now is...



is he going to post the finale, or wait until someone actually hits on the truth?



I hadn't realized the MAC track...

Thought the "must be a mole" was obvious (after all, someone had to place that WAP, and the room is/was secure...)



Unless....the back door opens up right to the street?

Who's to say that someone didn't, somehow, wait until it was "propped" open (as they may have noticed on a drive-by at some point), popped in and placed the WAP (what cojones!).  As (s)he drives by each day to work, they stop at a stoplight right by the back door.  Their laptop fires off it's spam...light turns green and  they're gone.



Network settings, subnet, etc still coulda been got via DHCP initially, and then once jotted down the WAP woulda been reconfigured as a bridge.  Wait...did we find out whether DHCP was available on that subnet?  Oh yeah, and it's outside the firewall, so probably not.



Oh well, it was a good conspiracy theory despite the holes.

(not that that ever stopped Ollie Stone... =^)) )</span>
		</div>
           
    <div class="spacer"></div>

    <div class="rule-gray"></div>
    <div class="spacer-small"></div>

    
